# 6. 彼女の歌声

An: ...
Miku: An, is something bothering you? You've been staring up at that wall for a while now.
An: Oh! Hi, Miku...! Haha. You caught me.
An: How do I put it...? Knowing that this is how we perceive RAD WEEKEND has me thinking about a lot.
An: Like how tall it is.
An: Aunt Nagi and everyone really did put on a legendary event.
Miku: An...
An: But...
An: We'll surpass it. For sure.
An: And I'll need to do what I have to to make that happen.
Miku: What you have to do...
Miku: Do you think you'll be able to?
An: Yeah.
An: All that's left for me to do is act when the time comes.
Miku: I see.
An: That being said...
An: I still don't have an answer for the thing that's really got me hung up.
Miku: Are you talking about...Kohane?
An: Yeah.
An: We're gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND and see what it's like beyond that dream. We're gonna do the thing Aunt Nagi didn't get to. I don't have any doubt about that.
An: But I still don't know what to do about how I feel about Kohane...
An: She's my partner... She means more to me than anyone else...
An: Because I wanna keep up with her.
An: So...
An: I wanna get closure on this before we surpass RAD WEEKEND.
An: Because we definitely won't be able to if I still have lingering doubts.
Miku: Right.
Miku: I'll be watching.
An: Huh?
Miku: I'll be keeping an eye on how you deal with this.
Miku: So, I'll be looking forward to seeing some nice results.
An: Thanks! I hope you'll be ready then!
An: Hey... Did you hear that just now?
Miku: Yes... Oh...!
An: ...! There's a crack in the wall!
An: A pretty big one too... But why now all of a sudden...?
???: ♪————...
An: Huh...?
Miku: Is someone...singing?
Miku: (But it doesn't sound like Kohane or any of the others. Who could it—)
An: That...voice...
Miku: An?
An: It can't be... But, it is...!
Miku: (I hear footsteps...getting closer.)
Miku: (Is that...?)
An: Aunt...Nagi...?
???: ♪————...
An: *Gasp*
An: Wait... Wait, please!
Miku: An...!
An: (Aunt Nagi... Aunt Nagi...!)
An: (What's she doing here?! I mean, she's...!)
An: (But if she is, who was that...?)
An: (Did my feelings...?)
An: (If so... Was that Aunt Nagi like a ghost or something...?)
An: (Still...!)
An: Aunt Nagi! Wait for me!!!
